Durban - A 16-year-old boy drowned at Nyoni Pools in Amanzimtoti on the South Coast on Sunday. Netcare 911 spokesperson Shawn Herbst said around 1pm on Sunday paramedics responded to reports of a drowning. "Reports from the scene indicate that a 16-year-old male was found unresponsive by bathers. Lifeguards were alerted who immediately started CPR after finding him unresponsive and not breathing." Herbst said the patient was treated on scene by an Advanced life support paramedic and rapidly transported to a hospital for further treatment. In a separate incident, a 4-year-old boy got into difficulty while swimming at a tidal pool in Salt Rock. IPSS Medical Rescue, together with KwaDukuza Lifeguards and NSRI responded to the incident. A spokesperson for IPSS Medica Rescue Paul Herbst said on arrival it was established that a member of the public had assisted the boy that had got into difficulty whilst in the pool. "The young boy showed symptoms of non-fatal drowning and was transported to a hospital by IPSS Medical Rescue for further care." Daily News